text: A newly opened coffee shop and the family decided to try some of the stalls out today. Pretty disappointed with what we tried today. We had the chicken rice, Chinese mixed rice and minced meat sauce ramen. All tasted below average in our opinion. Good thing was the fact ghat itâ€™s new, hence the tables and environment was clean.

Typical new HDB coffeeshop

+Plenty of sheltered parking at Multi
Storey Carpark upstairs.
+ Many fans to cool down d urban heat
+ Many tables, including bigger round ones towards d rear, beyond d last stall
+ Clean

- Prices high in general, though budget meal available in at least one stall ($3 diced chicken braised rice at Mata Thai stall)
- Place lacks a fishball noodle stall
- Sole Western stall Abang Gemuk is pricey (no mains below $8.20)
- One stall still unoccupied as of 17 Sep 2024.

Tips
---
Tray return point is OUTSIDE d coffeeshop near Western stall

The coffee shop beverage staff (esp one plump looking aunty) is extremely rude and unpleasant. Keeps getting annoyed at customer like we owe them.

kopi o is 80c but beware if you order kopi (it is $ 1.40 if never take away and $1.60 if take away), almost double the price

The food is ok, but the beverage store is horrible, the worker there can't follow the basic oder and very rude.
Ordered teh si kosong less ice, and she wants to gove me teh si kosong full ice. Give customer attitude and not following customer requests, extremely horrible.
$2 breakfast set from 6am to 11am. Nothing special just a normal coffee toast breakfast but for $2
